On Saturday, August 12, 2006, at 11:58AM, Mike Benthin <benthin(-at-)prodigy.net> wrote:

>78 bus- adjustors are too siezed to move, so I want to pull the drum
>and free/lube them.......but it's a catch 22- the drum will not come off 
>even with the suggested mallet tapping (rust/worn in edge holding it?) 

The drum can seize at the base of the stub axle cone (where the face of the drum meets the hub). Try some penetrating fluid there.

>and I can't back off the shoe adjustment- any other trick here?

If the adjusters won't move, try the same there: penetrating fluid.

